Kenya’s Benchmark Coffee Grade Rises 2.8%, Exchange Says

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-06-28T19:52:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/kenya-s-benchmark-coffee-grade-rises-2-8-exchange-says-1-.html
Kenya ’s benchmark coffee grade rose
2.8 percent at an auction today, the first in more than two
months, according to the Nairobi Coffee Exchange.  The top arabica AA grade sold for an average of $417.42 for
a 50-kilogram (110-pound) bag, up from $405.97 at the previous
auction April 19, the exchange said in an e-mailed report today.
Supplies of the grade rose 28 percent to 1,869 bags.  The average price for all coffee sold rose 5.8 percent to
$311.67 per bag, the exchange said. Sales rose 15 percent to
11,495 bags worth $4.38 million, from 9,961 bags valued at $3.59
million at the previous sale, it said.  The East African nation harvests the bulk of its crop from
October through December, while a secondary crop is reaped from
April to June. The following are details of today’s auction in
